Docs: Rect is shorthand for Rectangle{Pt(x0, y0), Pt(x1, y1)}. The returned
rectangle has minimum and maximum coordinates swapped if necessary so that

Funcs.Name: Rect

Funcs.Signature: func RegisterFormat(name string, magic string, decode func(io.Reader) (Image, error), decodeConfig func(io.Reader) (Config, error))
Docs: RegisterFormat registers an image format for use by Decode.
Name is the name of the format, like "jpeg" or "png".
Magic is the magic prefix that identifies the format's encoding. The magic
string can contain "?" wildcards that each match any one byte.
Decode is the function that decodes the encoded image.
DecodeConfig is the function that decodes just its configuration.
Funcs.Name: RegisterFormat
